Section1.Para:
The deposition velocity is then calculated as a sum of deposition velocities due to four main processes: Brownian diffusion (v

                  dif
                ), interception (v

                  int
                ), inertial impaction (v

                  imp
                ) and gravitational settling (v

                  s
                ). The Brownian motion deflects a particle from the streamlines, passing collectors so it can be captured. The interception occurs when a particle streamline happens to be closer to the collectors surface than the particle radius. The deposition by impaction occurs when a particle due to its inertia cannot follow a streamline bypassing a collector and hits it.
